Eptifibatide
fields.notes: Cyclic heptapeptide based on the integrin-binding loop sequence of the disintegrin barbourin, found in the venom of the southeastern pygmy rattlesnake (Sistrurus miliarius barbouri). Eptifibatide is an RGD-mimetic, reversively inhibiting platelet adhesion.

fields.name: Abciximab
fields.notes: A Fab fragment of the chimeric human-murine monoclonal antibody 7E3. Inhibits platelet aggregation by preventing the binding of fibrinogen, von Willebrand factor, and other adhesive molecules to integrin αIIb/β3. It also binds to integrin αv/β3 found on platelets and vessel wall endothelial and smooth muscle cells.

fields.name: Tirofiban
fields.notes: Synthetic, non-peptide inhibitor. Developed from a lead compound discovered in focused screening of small molecule replacements of the key RGD subunit of fibrinogen. Tirofiban is the first drug candidate whose origins can be traced to a pharmacophore-based virtual screening lead.

fields.name: Efalizumab
fields.notes: Recombinant humanized monoclonal antibody that binds to the alpha subunit of integrin alpha-L/beta-2. Acts as an immunosuppressant by inhibiting lymphocyte activation and cell migration out of blood vessels into tissues. Efalizumab was associated with fatal brain infections and was withdrawn from the market.

fields.name: Natalizumab
fields.notes: Humanized monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of multiple sclerosis and Crohn's disease. Natalizumab was previously named Antegren. Works by reducing the ability of inflammatory immune cells to attach to and pass through the cell layers lining the intestines and blood–brain barrier.

fields.name: Vedolizumab
fields.notes: Humanized monoclonal antibody used in the treatment of ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease. Has gut-selective anti-inflammatory activity, but also showed efficacy in SIV treatment and consequently has promise in HIV treatment in combination with antiretroviral therapy.
